# digitalSandboxLib
Arduino Library for the Digital Sandbox

The Digital Sandbox is a pre-wired Arduino board. It has multiple inputs and outputs that are directly connected to the microcontroller. The Digital Sandbox can be programmed using either the *SparkFun DigitalSandbox* board definition or using the *Arduino Fio* board selection in Arduino.

The Digital Sandbox (DS) has:

* pin 13 debug LED
* 5 LED bar graph on pins 4 - 8
* RGB LED on pins 9, 10, and 11
* temperature sensor
* light sensor
* sound sensor
* a push button 
* slide switch 
* slide potentiometer
* I2C auxiliary port with pins for A4 and A5
* pin 3 expansion port with a MOSFET driver to connect motors and a buzzer directly.

![](https://cdn.sparkfun.com//assets/parts/9/3/5/0/Digital_Sandbox.jpg)

To make it easier to use the Digital Sandbox, all pinModes are set with the 
instantiation of the digitalSandbox class. In addition, methods are added
to simplify the manipulation of the LEDs and pins on the board. 

To install this library, download the .zip file. 

Open up Arduino. Go to: Sketch>>Include Library>>Add .ZIP Library...

Navigate to your downloads folder or where you downloaded the library, and select the file you just downloaded.

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bhuangSFE/digitalSandboxLib/gh-pages/images/IncludeZIPlibrary.png)
***

These methods can be found in the .h file, but are here for reference:

    void setupSandbox();          // setups up pins and Serial.begin(9600);

    void blink(byte pinNum); 
    void blink(byte pinNum, unsigned int delayTime); 

    void leds(byte led4, byte led5, byte led6, byte led7, byte led8); // sets the state of all 5 LEDs
    void ledOn(byte pinNum);
    void ledOff(byte pinNum);
    void setRGB(byte red, byte green, byte blue);
	
    void ledOn(byte pinNum, unsigned int delayTime);
    void ledOff(byte pinNum, unsigned int delayTime);	
    void setRGB(byte red, byte green, byte blue, unsigned int delayTime);

    unsigned int readSlider();
    unsigned int readSound();
    unsigned int readLight();
    unsigned int readTemp();
    boolean readButton();
    boolean readSwitch();

